  "footnotes": [
    {
      "id": "1",
      "text": "A breadth subject is a subject chosen from outside a student’s main research area, intended to expand their knowledge base, strengthen interdisciplinary thinking, and provide contextual or methodological skills that enhance their primary field of study. CEE recommends 1.976 Graduate Professional Development Seminar but other subjects are acceptable with advisor approval."
    },
    {
      "id": "2",
      "text": "Thesis units are based on the average duration of the doctoral program (five years) but will vary based on how long the student remains in the program."
    }
  ],
